<section class=3D"moneyfit-faqs" id=3D"vacation-faqs">
  <h2>Calculator FAQs</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>What expenses should I include in my vacation budget?</summary=
>
    <div class=3D"faq-answer">
      Include all major categories: airfare or transport, lodging, meals, a=
ctivities, souvenirs, and any hidden fees (e.g., resort fees, baggage fees)=
. Don=E2=80=99t forget miscellaneous costs like travel insurance or local t=
ransit.
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>How do I estimate variable costs like food or entertainment?</=
summary>
    <div class=3D"faq-answer">
      Use average per-day benchmarks for meals and attractions in your dest=
ination. Research restaurant prices and ticket fees ahead of time, then mul=
tiply by the number of days. Adjust upward if you plan specialty experience=
s or fine dining.
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>How far in advance should I start saving?</summary>
    <div class=3D"faq-answer">
      Ideally, begin budgeting 3=E2=80=936 months before your trip. This ti=
meframe allows you to spread out savings and take advantage of early-bookin=
g discounts for flights and lodging, reducing overall costs.
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>What if my timeline to save changes?</summary>
    <div class=3D"faq-answer">
      Simply update the =E2=80=9Cmonths until vacation=E2=80=9D field in th=
e calculator. It will recalculate your required monthly savings. If your ti=
meframe shortens, you may need to adjust expenses or increase savings to st=
ay on track.
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Do I need to register or log in?</summary>
    <div class=3D"faq-answer">
      No=E2=80=94this tool is free to use without any sign-up. Enter your e=
xpected expenses and timeline to instantly get a personalized vacation budg=
et estimate.
    </div>
  </details>
</section>

